    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.38",
      "en": "From the official logo guidelines",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.39",
      "en": "Minimum clear space around the logo or symbol is 2× the height of the mark on every side (sometimes described as “doubling the height”). The payoff lockup uses the same rule.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.4",
      "en": "Trademark and legal wording: follow the full guidelines and counsel for ® notices, territory, and contractual use.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.40",
      "en": "Each band sets a maximum width for print and screen and the lockup to use at that scale (full payoff, horizontal wordmark, or symbol only).",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.41",
      "en": "Do not scale the full payoff into the small band — switch to the symbol. Match ink and field colours to the logo section above.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.42",
      "en": "Don’t — examples from the guidelines (not exhaustive)",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.43",
      "en": "The logo must not use colours outside the identity palette.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.44",
      "en": "The logo must not be used as a hollow outline.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.45",
      "en": "Do not distort, stretch, or compress the mark.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.46",
      "en": "Do not tilt, rotate, or otherwise skew the logo.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.47",
      "en": "No lighting, drop shadows, or bevels on the lockup.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.48",
      "en": "The logotype must not use a different colour from the symbol.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.49",
      "en": "Common sense applies: if it hurts legibility or looks unlike the master files, don’t ship it.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.5",
      "en": "Mark, spacing, and contrast",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.50",
      "en": "Co-branding layout",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.51",
      "en": "When appearing alongside another company, give both marks adequate clear space and balanced visual weight. A typical row is: Partner — Elemento , without merging or overlapping the lockups.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.52",
      "en": "Request the full partnership artwork from hello@elemento.cloud for approved templates and lockups.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.53",
      "en": "Primary and secondary brand colours",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.54",
      "en": "Use these first for maximum recognition. The site theme also uses nearby neutrals (e.g. #1A1C20 for body text) — pair brand primaries with accessible contrast.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.55",
      "en": "Product UI tokens on elemento.cloud may differ slightly; treat this page as the marketing colour reference and css/themes.css for implementation.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.56",
      "en": "Brand type stack (with live-site note)",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.57",
      "en": "Headings use Red Hat Display (often Extrabold). Key words inside headings may use Argent Pixel Italic ( Connary Fagen — Argent Pixel ). Body copy should use Red Hat Text — do not substitute Display for long text. Code uses Red Hat Mono ( Google Fonts ). Icons on elemento.cloud pair Font Awesome with a bundled Pixel Icon Library webfont for pixel-style glyphs ( .hn classes; files under assets/font/PixelIconLibrary/ ). Check each source's licensing before reusing or redistributing.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.58",
      "en": "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz 1234567890",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.59",
      "en": "Headings — guidelines recommend Extrabold. Google Fonts .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.6",
      "en": "Layout preference: use the horizontal payoff whenever possible (wordmark, tagline, and ® ). When width is tight — mobile headers, narrow columns — use the vertical payoff lockup instead. For avatars, favicons, and compact UI, use the symbol alone (no wordmark).",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.60",
      "en": "Highlight within headings",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.61",
      "en": "Accent inside titles only. Argent Pixel is licensed from Connary Fagen; this site ships it for select treatments.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.62",
      "en": "Body text must stay functional and highly legible. Red Hat Text is tuned for paragraphs — different geometry from Display.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.63",
      "en": "Canonical brand body font per guidelines. elemento.cloud still uses Open Sans in many templates; new work should align with Red Hat Text over time.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.64",
      "en": "nucleus cluster status api.elemento.cloud/v1",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.65",
      "en": "Code, CLI samples, and technical UI.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.66",
      "en": "Patterns, icons & photography",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.67",
      "en": "Visual identity uses patterns inspired by the “force of cloud” — dynamic, physics-adjacent motifs. Use approved pattern files from the brand kit; don’t redraw from memory.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.68",
      "en": "This site implements UI and marketing icons with Font Awesome and pixel-style accents via the bundled Pixel Icon Library webfont ( .hn icon classes in assets/font/PixelIconLibrary/ ). Treat that pairing as the standard for elemento.cloud ; avoid ad-hoc third icon families. Keep stroke, corner radius, and colour usage consistent with the chosen set.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.69",
      "en": "Retro-future — abstract concepts, atmospheric or space-research imagery. Team moments — people and culture for tone of voice. Moving images — long exposure and dynamic shots for energy. Avoid generic stock that fights these three lanes.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.7",
      "en": "The logo palette defines three ink colours — Starter Yellow #FFA600 , Crystal White #F8F8FF , and Void Black #16161D — on the appropriate field. Each variant below shows those inks on the correct field: horizontal payoff , vertical payoff , then symbol only (yellow on void black is preferred).",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.70",
      "en": "Spellings and capitalization",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.71",
      "en": "Company and platform name: Elemento (sentence case in body; title case in headings as on the site). When you need the full legal line with Modular Cloud and ® , use the horizontal or vertical payoff lockup according to space.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.72",
      "en": "Atomos , Electros , and Atomosphere — capitalize as proper nouns. Use each product’s SVG from All products alongside the name when possible.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.73",
      "en": "Email hello@elemento.cloud for high-resolution files or co-marketing review.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.brand-guidelines.p.8",
      "en": "Wordmark + tagline + ®",
      "it": "",
      "source": "brand-guidelines.html",
      "context": "<p>"
